      <bioghist id="aspace_216a1653dfec30f9e6a239a9ec6bc97e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Anna Fuller Fund and Anna Fuller Memorial Prize were established in 1932 by the bequest of Egbert Chaplain Fuller in honor of his wife who died of cancer in 1918. The aim of the fund, as outlined in Fuller's will, is "to alleviate suffering from disease, through: (a) research as to its cause, treatment and care; (b) the education of the public as to its prevention and treatment; and (c) the actual treatment of persons suffering from disease. My chief interest is in the alleviation of suffering from cancer..."</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7d13b580f8906937ba5ce6a135ac7623">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of grant reports, financial records, and correspondence documenting the status and recipients of the Anna Fuller Fund and the Anna Fuller Prize. Included is a photocopy of Egbert C. Fuller's will.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_663a0c41c83f0801d9d3a5206fda7345">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged in two series: I. Reports and Miscellaneous Projects. II. Anna Fuller Grants.</p>  
      </arrangement>
